5
Ex. No: 2
Date: Write a PHP programs that uses arrays and functions in PHP
Aim:
Write a PHP programs that uses arrays and functions in PHP.
Array in PHP
 An array stores multiple values in one single variable
 In PHP, there are three kinds of arrays:
o Numeric array
o Associative array
o Multidimensional array
Numeric Array in PHP
Numeric array is an array with a numeric index
Numeric Array Example
<?php
$colors = array("Red", "Green", "Blue");
// Accessing elements
echo $colors[0];
echo $colors[1];
echo $colors[2];
?>
OUTPUT:
Red Green Blue
Associative array in PHP
Associative array is an array where each ID key is associated with a value
Associative array Example
<?php
$person = array(
"first_name" => "John",
"last_name" => "Doe",
"age" => 30
);
echo $person["first_name"];
echo $person["last_name"];
echo $person["age"];
?>
OUTPUT:
John Doe 30
6
Loop through an Associative Array
Using foreach Loop
<?php
$person = array(
"first_name" => "John",
"last_name" => "Doe",
"age" => 30,
"email" => "john.doe@example.com"
);
foreach ($person as $key => $value) {
echo "Key: $key, Value: $value\n";
}
?>
OUTPUT:
Key: first_name, Value: John
Key: last_name, Value: Doe
Key: age, Value: 30
Key: email, Value: john.doe@example.com
Using for Loop with array_keys
<?php
$person = array(
"first_name" => "John",
"last_name" => "Doe",
"age" => 30,
"email" => "john.doe@example.com"
);
$keys = array_keys($person);
for ($i = 0; $i < count($keys); $i++) {
$key = $keys[$i];
$value = $person[$key];
echo "Key: $key, Value: $value\n";
}
?>
OUTPUT:
Key: first_name, Value: John
Key: last_name, Value: Doe
Key: age, Value: 30
Key: email, Value: john.doe@example.com
7
Multidimensional array in PHP
Multidimensional array is an array containing one or more arrays
<?php
$contacts = array(
array(
"name" => "Peter Parker",
"email" => "peterparker@mail.com",
),
array(
"name" => "Clark Kent",
"email" => "clarkkent@mail.com",
),
array(
"name" => "Harry Potter",
"email" => "harrypotter@mail.com",
)
);
echo "Peter Parker's Email-id is: " . $contacts[0]["email"];
?>
OUTPUT:
Peter Parker's Email-id is: peterparker@mail.com
Viewing Array Structure and Values
<?php
$cities = array("London", "Paris", "New York");
Print_r($cities);
var_dump($cities);
?>
Output:
Array ( [0] => London [1] => Paris [2] => New York )
array(3) { [0]=> string(6) "London" [1]=> string(5) "Paris" [2]=> string(8) "New York" }
8
User Defined Function in PHP
Functions are group of statements that can perform a task
Syntax:
function functionName()
{
code to be executed;
}
User Defined Function
<html>
<body>
<?php
function whatIsToday(){
echo "Today is " . date('l', mktime());
}
whatIsToday();
?>
</body>
</html>
OUTPUT:
Today is Tuesday
PHP Functions - Adding parameters
<html>
<body>
<?php
function getSum($num1, $num2){
$sum = $num1 + $num2;
echo "Sum of the two numbers $num1 and $num2 is : $sum";
}
getSum(10, 20);
?>
</body>
</html>
OUTPUT:
Sum of the two numbers 10 and 20 is : 30
9
Swap Numbers PHP Example
<?php
$a = 5;
$b = 10;
echo "Before swapping:\n";
echo "a = $a\n";
echo "b = $b\n";
$temp = $a;
$a = $b;
$b = $temp;
echo "After swapping:\n";
echo "a = $a\n";
echo "b = $b\n";
?>
OUTPUT:
Before swapping:
a = 5
b = 10
After swapping:
a = 10
b = 5
PHP Functions - Return values
<html>
<body>
<?php
function getSum($num1, $num2){
$total = $num1 + $num2;
return $total;
}
echo getSum(5, 10);
?>
</body>
</html>
OUTPUT:
15
